## 5. Request Detail View

When a homeowner clicks a request from "My Requests," they see a full detail page containing:
- Request status and metadata
- Uploaded supporting documents (file name, description, upload date)
- Conditions (if "Approved with Conditions") — listed clearly
- Message thread (same as Communications tab, scoped to this request)
- Ability to reply to the ARC committee

---

## 6. Request Statuses

| Status | Description |
|---|---|
| Draft | Created but not yet submitted |
| Under Review / Pending Review | Submitted, awaiting ARC decision |
| Approved | Fully approved with no conditions |
| Approved w/ Conditions | Approved, but homeowner and contractor must comply with stated conditions |
| Denied | Request rejected |
| Completed | Construction finished and passed final inspection |
| Overdue | 30-day review window has elapsed without a decision |

---

## 7. Notifications

- Toast notification on successful submission
- Notification bell (in-app) for status changes and new messages
- Future: email and/or SMS notifications when ARC committee responds

---

## 8. Legal Compliance Requirements

- The system must cite **NC GS §47F-3-107** (30-day review rule) wherever relevant
- The neighbor notification requirement must be surfaced before submission and confirmed by checkbox
- Overdue status must be flagged automatically after 30 days with no decision
- The system should provide homeowners with relevant rules and approved materials **before** they submit to reduce rejections

---

## 9. Back-Office (ARC Committee) Requirements

> Scope: the following are requirements for the back-office / admin view (separate from the resident portal).

- View all submitted ARC requests across the community
- Review request details, documents, and photos
- Add comments visible to the homeowner
- Issue a decision: Approve / Approve with Conditions / Deny
- Specify conditions when approving with conditions (conditions must be forwarded to the contractor)
- Respond in the message thread
- Track review deadlines and receive overdue alerts

---

## 10. Out of Scope for Version 1

- WhatsApp / SMS channel integration (communications are in-app and email only)
- Contractor portal access (contractor communication is mediated via the ARC committee and homeowner message thread)
- Automatic email threading (unique-email-per-conversation is a future enhancement)
- Appeal workflow

